WEBVTT

00:05.804 --> 00:08.546
[dramatic music plays]

00:08.632 --> 00:11.417
♪ ♪

00:28.472 --> 00:29.342
- [person] Oi!
- [gasps]

00:31.692 --> 00:33.477
You the one they call It?

00:33.607 --> 00:34.869
Actually, I've got a name.

00:35.000 --> 00:36.784
Cook wants ya.

00:36.914 --> 00:37.915
Why?

00:38.002 --> 00:39.699
Fucked if I know.

00:39.829 --> 00:41.961
[indistinct chatter]

00:42.092 --> 00:44.921
[sighs]

00:45.049 --> 00:47.834
[pensive music plays]

00:48.008 --> 00:50.750
♪ ♪

00:53.664 --> 00:56.449
[indistinct chatter]

00:56.623 --> 00:59.322
♪ ♪

01:07.066 --> 01:09.198
[items clattering]

01:09.327 --> 01:10.806
[Cook] You, stop!

01:10.937 --> 01:12.417
Here.

01:12.548 --> 01:14.420
Don't keep the queen waiting.

01:14.984 --> 01:16.595
You want me to serve the queen?

01:16.723 --> 01:19.683
She needs a new maid
for her son's coronation.

01:19.812 --> 01:21.510
She's seeing everyone
until she makes up her mind.

01:21.597 --> 01:23.512
So move!

01:23.643 --> 01:25.297
Now, where are my ramekins?

01:25.382 --> 01:27.210
Don't look in a mirror.

01:27.343 --> 01:28.996
Could suck the soul
right out of you.

01:29.126 --> 01:30.432
I don't believe in all that.

01:30.562 --> 01:31.781
Your funeral.

01:31.911 --> 01:34.653
[dramatic music plays]

01:34.739 --> 01:36.480
♪ ♪

01:36.610 --> 01:38.612
- [indistinct chatter]
- [footman whistles]

01:38.740 --> 01:39.915
[footman] Hello.

01:40.047 --> 01:41.396
Hello there.

01:41.526 --> 01:42.483
What's your name?

01:42.616 --> 01:43.573
Show us your tits.

01:43.702 --> 01:44.529
[clicks tongue]

01:44.658 --> 01:47.096
[laughter]

01:48.357 --> 01:49.793
[footman] Come on!

01:49.966 --> 01:52.751
♪ ♪

01:55.582 --> 01:56.496
I'm not going in there.

01:57.928 --> 01:59.800
[knocking on door]

01:59.931 --> 02:00.671
[person] Enter.

02:00.758 --> 02:02.108
[door creaks]

02:04.586 --> 02:07.328
♪ ♪

02:12.939 --> 02:14.419
Drew the short straw, did you?

02:30.953 --> 02:31.998
What's your name?

02:35.782 --> 02:38.394
They call me It, ma'am.

02:38.523 --> 02:39.872
Do they?

02:40.005 --> 02:42.268
Well...

02:42.397 --> 02:43.528
that's not very nice.

02:43.660 --> 02:44.922
[It] No.

02:45.051 --> 02:46.140
They're not, actually.

02:47.923 --> 02:49.925
Very nice, that is.

02:50.053 --> 02:52.491
Well, I'm sure
you'll get your own back.

02:52.623 --> 02:53.581
I pray for their souls.

02:55.667 --> 02:57.277
As I pray for yours.

02:58.235 --> 02:59.410
I'm grateful.

03:01.669 --> 03:04.976
Though...

03:05.064 --> 03:06.283
it might feel better
to get your own back

03:06.415 --> 03:07.503
every once in a while.

03:09.329 --> 03:10.634
You look hungry.

03:17.812 --> 03:19.466
You've heard too many stories.

03:19.596 --> 03:22.251
[orange peel tearing]

03:52.232 --> 03:53.625
In a week's time,

03:53.755 --> 03:56.236
my second son, Charles IX,

03:56.366 --> 03:58.411
will be crowned king of France.

03:58.540 --> 04:00.672
For the next seven days,

04:00.804 --> 04:02.414
I'm to be consumed

04:02.544 --> 04:03.632
with preparations for pageantry.

04:04.936 --> 04:07.112
Feasts, balls,

04:07.242 --> 04:09.375
decorations.

04:09.506 --> 04:12.117
All the details that are
supposed to entertain a woman.

04:12.724 --> 04:14.073
But they do not entertain me.

04:16.248 --> 04:20.774
Therefore, I would like
somebody to... distract me

04:20.904 --> 04:22.733
with conversation.

04:23.561 --> 04:24.779
Perhaps that person
could be you.

04:26.517 --> 04:27.692
Me?

04:27.779 --> 04:29.172
You remind me of myself

04:29.260 --> 04:30.914
when I first came
to this country.

04:31.043 --> 04:33.132
[scoffs softly]

04:33.218 --> 04:34.349
You don't believe me.

04:36.874 --> 04:39.573
Well, you're the queen.

04:40.312 --> 04:42.749
And you are just
a poor little servant girl

04:42.876 --> 04:45.227
who doesn't even have a name.

04:49.317 --> 04:50.231
Rahima.

04:50.318 --> 04:52.015
Well, Rahima...

04:53.188 --> 04:54.842
...I'll let you in
on a little secret, shall I?

04:56.798 --> 04:58.583
I used to be just like you.

04:58.670 --> 05:00.715
[somber music plays]

05:00.847 --> 05:04.154
Someone else's shoes
upon my feet,

05:04.283 --> 05:07.243
shivering myself to sleep
at night,

05:07.373 --> 05:09.810
with nobody in the world
to care about me.

05:09.894 --> 05:13.028
♪ ♪

05:13.158 --> 05:14.334
So the only question is...

05:20.036 --> 05:21.646
...what are you willing to do
to change it?

05:23.080 --> 05:24.821
Turn the other cheek?

05:25.909 --> 05:27.737
Pray for those
who have trespassed against me?

05:27.823 --> 05:30.652
♪ ♪

05:30.783 --> 05:31.827
Well...

05:33.783 --> 05:34.958
...I'll tell you
a little story...

05:36.741 --> 05:37.873
...and...

05:39.614 --> 05:42.181
...you can tell me

05:42.269 --> 05:44.053
what you would have done
differently.

05:44.140 --> 05:45.750
How does that sound?

05:45.880 --> 05:48.578
[dramatic music plays]

05:48.751 --> 05:49.752
♪ ♪

05:49.882 --> 05:51.753
Then I'll begin.

05:51.884 --> 05:53.233
I was born of wealthy parents...

05:53.364 --> 05:54.887
[baby crying]

05:54.973 --> 05:56.670
...the wealthiest commoners
in Europe.

05:58.627 --> 06:00.106
For that, my family was envied

06:00.195 --> 06:01.762
and despised in equal measure.

06:02.850 --> 06:04.504
[people moaning]

06:04.633 --> 06:06.156
But my father had a weakness.

06:06.330 --> 06:09.507
♪ ♪

06:09.637 --> 06:10.942
Syphilis drove him to his death

06:11.074 --> 06:12.641
within a year of my birth.

06:14.857 --> 06:17.033
My mother,
infected with the same,

06:17.120 --> 06:18.600
followed soon after.

06:20.080 --> 06:21.386
My grandmother took me in.

06:21.515 --> 06:22.908
[glass shatters]

06:23.038 --> 06:25.606
[baby crying]

06:25.692 --> 06:28.391
She died in her sleep
a few months later.

06:31.175 --> 06:32.698
You might say I was bad luck.

06:32.871 --> 06:35.570
♪ ♪

06:35.698 --> 06:37.483
[person]
...will be done on Earth

06:37.613 --> 06:39.963
as it is in heaven.

06:40.094 --> 06:42.357
- Amen.
- [children] Amen.

06:42.487 --> 06:43.575
[Catherine] I was raised
along with the rest

06:43.706 --> 06:45.708
of the unwanted children.

06:45.880 --> 06:49.144
♪ ♪

06:49.273 --> 06:52.058
Like you, I believed
that if I were good,

06:52.189 --> 06:52.972
God would protect me.

06:53.146 --> 06:55.323
♪ ♪

06:55.451 --> 06:56.713
I was wrong.

06:56.889 --> 06:59.109
♪ ♪

06:59.235 --> 07:00.933
Look familiar?

07:01.063 --> 07:03.892
[indistinct chatter]

07:04.022 --> 07:04.762
[knocking on door]

07:06.807 --> 07:09.462
"Trust in the Lord
with all your heart

07:09.593 --> 07:11.072
and do not lean on your own"...

07:11.204 --> 07:12.248
You're late.

07:13.247 --> 07:14.161
Wait a moment.

07:22.386 --> 07:24.127
Where is my orange?

07:24.255 --> 07:26.562
The markets were emptied.

07:26.692 --> 07:28.302
The soldiers
have ransacked Florence.

07:28.434 --> 07:29.260
People are starving...

07:29.390 --> 07:30.696
Silence!

07:30.825 --> 07:32.044
Come closer.

07:33.653 --> 07:34.872
Closer!

07:35.004 --> 07:37.355
[sniffing]

07:38.962 --> 07:41.094
[grunts]

07:41.224 --> 07:42.225
Ow.

07:42.357 --> 07:43.488
Get me the switch.

07:45.707 --> 07:46.751
- [dog whines]
- [Mother Superior] Do as I say,

07:46.880 --> 07:48.577
or you'll have it yourself.

07:49.664 --> 07:52.406
Medici bitch,
I'll teach you to lie to me.

07:52.538 --> 07:53.582
[Catherine gasps]

07:54.975 --> 07:58.892
♪ ♪

08:00.195 --> 08:02.241
[Catherine] I have always had
a strong imagination,

08:02.370 --> 08:04.633
as if I could see things
before they happen.

08:04.763 --> 08:07.244
[dog whines]

08:07.375 --> 08:09.942
Sometimes it feels like
I can make them happen...

08:10.027 --> 08:11.942
[Mother Superior]
Now get out of my sight!

08:12.075 --> 08:13.772
[Catherine] ...if I want them
badly enough.

08:13.902 --> 08:15.425
[Catherine groans]

08:15.598 --> 08:18.166
♪ ♪

08:21.908 --> 08:23.039
Get me my dog.

08:23.211 --> 08:25.910
♪ ♪

08:32.090 --> 08:34.092
It's dead.

08:35.179 --> 08:36.789
It's a quality
some people don't appreciate.

08:39.441 --> 08:41.138
Though I might have
behaved differently

08:41.270 --> 08:42.924
had I known
the risks the nuns were taking

08:43.051 --> 08:44.270
having me under their roof.

08:44.401 --> 08:46.403
[bells tolling]

08:46.531 --> 08:49.360
[distressed chatter]

08:49.492 --> 08:52.277
[tense music plays]

08:52.363 --> 08:55.148
♪ ♪

08:58.411 --> 09:00.587
[distressed chatter continues]

09:00.761 --> 09:03.546
♪ ♪

09:07.288 --> 09:08.376
[nun] No, no, no, no, no!

09:08.506 --> 09:10.986
Oh, please! No, stop!

09:11.118 --> 09:12.598
No!

09:12.727 --> 09:15.643
[distressed chatter continues]

09:15.774 --> 09:19.168
[people clamoring]

09:19.254 --> 09:22.432
♪ ♪

09:22.561 --> 09:24.868
[Catherine] Apparently, my head
was still worth something

09:24.996 --> 09:26.650
to the starving soldiers
of Florence.

09:26.780 --> 09:29.173
Where is the Medici bitch?

09:29.260 --> 09:30.697
[Mother Superior]
This is a house of God!

09:30.828 --> 09:32.134
I suggest you leave immediately.

09:33.482 --> 09:35.484
Then I suggest you fuck off.

09:35.612 --> 09:36.787
[nun] Oh, Mother!

09:38.311 --> 09:39.965
[person] Upstairs now!

09:40.051 --> 09:41.487
[gasps]

09:41.617 --> 09:44.358
[distressed chatter]

09:44.533 --> 09:47.971
♪ ♪

09:48.101 --> 09:50.887
- [nun] Let her go! Let her go!
- [person] Shut it, old lady.

09:50.974 --> 09:54.194
♪ ♪

09:54.715 --> 09:56.543
[person]
She's up here! Come on!

09:56.671 --> 09:58.325
- [person] Now, where is she?
- [nun screams]

09:58.498 --> 10:00.848
♪ ♪

10:00.936 --> 10:02.111
[Mathilde] Hurry!

10:02.198 --> 10:03.112
[person] Open it!

10:03.198 --> 10:05.462
[nun screams]

10:05.548 --> 10:06.679
[person] Move it! Come on!

10:06.854 --> 10:08.856
♪ ♪

10:13.379 --> 10:14.424
[Catherine] Cut it! Hurry!

10:14.556 --> 10:17.297
[nun gasping and sobbing]

10:17.472 --> 10:20.257
♪ ♪

10:29.479 --> 10:30.392
They're coming!

10:34.178 --> 10:36.528
Who amongst you would interfere
with a bride of Christ?

10:36.658 --> 10:39.399
[dramatic music plays]

10:39.574 --> 10:40.923
♪ ♪

10:41.008 --> 10:43.184
[Catherine grunts]

10:43.315 --> 10:46.536
That was the first time
I knew I mattered to anyone.

10:46.665 --> 10:49.406
[people clamoring]

10:57.239 --> 10:59.328
I had never before
left the convent.

11:00.328 --> 11:01.678
My first impression
of my fellow man

11:01.807 --> 11:03.287
was less than favorable.

11:03.417 --> 11:06.159
[indistinct chatter]

11:29.697 --> 11:30.959
Would you help me?

11:35.527 --> 11:38.268
♪ ♪

11:40.098 --> 11:41.839
Something tells me
you'll be all right.

11:43.534 --> 11:44.839
How would you know?

11:44.971 --> 11:46.886
I'm a fortune-teller.

11:47.057 --> 11:49.189
♪ ♪

11:54.804 --> 11:57.502
[indistinct chatter]

12:02.417 --> 12:04.288
[person speaking indistinctly]

12:04.418 --> 12:06.551
[person]
Make way for His Eminence.

12:06.681 --> 12:07.639
- [person gasps]
- [person] Do you see that?

12:07.769 --> 12:08.857
[person] What's he doing here?

12:08.986 --> 12:09.769
[person] Can you believe it?

12:09.900 --> 12:11.336
[person] It's the pope!

12:11.466 --> 12:13.556
[person] Look, look!
It's the pope!

12:13.687 --> 12:14.949
What is he doing here?

12:15.121 --> 12:17.907
♪ ♪

12:27.390 --> 12:29.610
Gentlemen...

12:29.697 --> 12:32.787
I believe you have something
that belongs to me.

12:32.917 --> 12:35.354
Until then, I thought
I was alone in the world.

12:38.705 --> 12:40.098
That is not close
to what we're owed.

12:41.313 --> 12:42.967
We bled for you.

12:45.404 --> 12:46.971
[Clement]
By the authority of the papacy,

12:47.100 --> 12:49.232
I command you to free her.

12:49.363 --> 12:52.192
[indistinct chatter]

12:52.322 --> 12:54.760
Or burn in hell
for all eternity.

12:54.845 --> 12:57.587
[tense music plays]

12:57.763 --> 13:00.504
♪ ♪

13:07.160 --> 13:09.902
[Catherine] My first taste
of the power of presentation

13:10.031 --> 13:12.120
made a lasting impression.

13:12.295 --> 13:15.037
♪ ♪

13:19.126 --> 13:19.953
Fuck it.

13:20.127 --> 13:22.390
♪ ♪

13:25.566 --> 13:27.307
Take her.

13:27.435 --> 13:28.741
She's not worth the bother.

13:38.923 --> 13:40.621
[Clement] My dear niece.

13:44.665 --> 13:45.840
[smooches]

13:45.972 --> 13:48.670
What have you done to your hair?

13:48.798 --> 13:51.496
[dramatic vocal music plays]

13:51.670 --> 13:54.412
♪ ♪

14:00.635 --> 14:01.853
[inhales sharply]

14:01.984 --> 14:04.421
[grunts softly]

14:04.551 --> 14:06.771
Forgive me. It's an...

14:06.898 --> 14:09.640
abscess on my exit.

14:09.769 --> 14:11.771
Makes riding a terror.

14:11.903 --> 14:12.991
[abscess squelches]

14:13.120 --> 14:14.208
[Clement groans]

14:14.297 --> 14:16.299
Anyway, I have wonderful news.

14:16.385 --> 14:17.952
Bit of a brain wave on my part.

14:18.037 --> 14:19.125
Your marriage has been arranged.

14:19.257 --> 14:21.172
[moans]

14:21.300 --> 14:23.259
- Marriage?
- Yes.

14:23.389 --> 14:25.609
There you are.

14:25.739 --> 14:27.784
Second son
of the king of France.

14:27.872 --> 14:31.397
Not a bad-looking kid if
you can trust the rendering.

14:31.525 --> 14:34.397
And a more flattering version
of your likeness

14:34.482 --> 14:37.137
was sent to Paris,
and that's been accepted.

14:37.223 --> 14:39.617
Now the only task remaining
is how to minimize...

14:39.705 --> 14:42.403
[groans]

14:42.489 --> 14:45.492
how to minimize
the disappointment of reality.

14:45.580 --> 14:48.061
I imagine you're aware you're
not very much to look at.

14:48.190 --> 14:49.844
[slurps]

14:49.930 --> 14:51.714
Mm, would you mind?

14:54.368 --> 14:55.935
Mm.

14:56.067 --> 14:58.069
[moans]

14:58.198 --> 15:00.679
[grunts]

15:00.764 --> 15:02.417
But such a shame

15:02.505 --> 15:04.943
that you didn't inherit
your mother's looks.

15:05.072 --> 15:05.943
[groans]

15:09.206 --> 15:10.468
Ah, thank you.

15:11.816 --> 15:14.036
[groans]

15:14.167 --> 15:16.082
I-I'm told you're intelligent,

15:16.212 --> 15:18.083
so that's good.

15:18.212 --> 15:20.562
Tends to last longer
than mere beauty.

15:20.693 --> 15:23.086
And luckily for us,
King of France has a passion

15:23.214 --> 15:24.955
for all things Italian.

15:25.087 --> 15:27.220
With you,
he gets a handful of duchies.

15:27.306 --> 15:30.048
Milan, Parma, Piacenza,
to be precise.

15:30.178 --> 15:31.963
[cardinal] As well as
the usual extortionate dowry.

15:32.091 --> 15:34.833
In return, we get protection

15:34.965 --> 15:38.011
against that slack-jawed
ingrate in Madrid

15:38.140 --> 15:39.489
who has done a bit of a number
on us of late,

15:39.620 --> 15:40.752
has he not, Cardinal?

15:40.880 --> 15:42.620
What if I don't want
to be married?

15:42.752 --> 15:44.972
[chuckles]

15:45.100 --> 15:47.189
I'll make this abundantly clear
to you.

15:48.974 --> 15:50.845
Our armies are beaten.

15:50.976 --> 15:52.978
Our soldiers
who didn't have the foresight

15:53.108 --> 15:54.631
to get themselves killed
on the field of battle

15:54.717 --> 15:57.067
are all starving.

15:57.197 --> 16:00.157
The people blame the maidages,

16:00.285 --> 16:02.679
which makes you
the orphan offspring

16:02.809 --> 16:05.246
of the most despised family
in Europe.

16:06.202 --> 16:08.117
And without
the protection of France,

16:08.206 --> 16:10.165
we will both find ourselves
hanging by our feet

16:10.295 --> 16:13.081
in the Campo de' Fiori
before very long.

16:13.167 --> 16:16.779
In short, it doesn't matter
what you want.

16:16.908 --> 16:18.866
Hmm? You understand?

16:19.866 --> 16:22.042
Hmm?

16:22.171 --> 16:23.825
Now, you won't be
entirely alone.

16:23.956 --> 16:26.524
A-a distant cousin
of your mother's,

16:26.652 --> 16:28.176
Diane de Poitiers,

16:28.307 --> 16:30.353
is highly regarded
in the Valois court,

16:30.483 --> 16:33.530
and I'm sure she will be
of some help to you.

16:33.658 --> 16:35.095
Now, I'm sorry,
but we have to make sure

16:35.225 --> 16:36.879
that you're intact, so...

16:39.447 --> 16:40.753
[Clement groans]

16:44.275 --> 16:45.624
Lean over.

16:45.755 --> 16:47.060
And raise your skirt.

16:50.455 --> 16:51.848
How is this different
to what the soldiers

16:51.976 --> 16:53.891
planned to do to me,
you're wondering.

16:53.980 --> 16:54.764
[whimpers]

16:56.371 --> 16:57.372
Not much.

16:58.328 --> 16:59.547
She's all there.

16:59.636 --> 17:00.463
[Clement] Excellent!

17:00.590 --> 17:01.330
In that case...

17:01.461 --> 17:02.636
[groans]

17:02.723 --> 17:03.855
...we don't have a moment
to lose.

17:07.076 --> 17:09.165
Your Grace, to what do I owe
the honor of my visit?

17:09.294 --> 17:12.210
My niece is to be married

17:12.339 --> 17:15.169
to the youngest son
of the king of France,

17:15.253 --> 17:16.820
and you will make her
the most beautiful bride

17:16.909 --> 17:18.258
the world has ever seen.

17:21.173 --> 17:22.958
I'm not a magician.

17:23.044 --> 17:25.611
[Clement]
Then I suggest you become one.

17:25.696 --> 17:26.915
You will be accompanying
my niece to France

17:27.047 --> 17:28.962
as her personal atelier.

17:29.089 --> 17:32.440
Red is not her color.

17:32.570 --> 17:34.790
We need more ornamentation
around the neckline

17:34.920 --> 17:36.617
to divert attention
from her chin.

17:36.749 --> 17:39.665
[sprightly music plays]

17:39.793 --> 17:42.404
Something refreshing about
being picked apart like that,

17:42.536 --> 17:44.321
something honest.

17:45.623 --> 17:47.060
I knew right away I was
in the hands of a professional.

17:47.148 --> 17:49.193
[Sebastio] She has nice ankles.

17:49.323 --> 17:51.412
Make sure every dress
is two inches shorter

17:51.541 --> 17:52.586
so they are always visible,

17:52.717 --> 17:55.024
along with these.

17:55.153 --> 17:56.371
All the rage in Asia.

17:56.548 --> 17:59.334
♪ ♪

18:01.899 --> 18:04.336
They shall highlight
your best feature.

18:04.465 --> 18:06.511
You must be prepared to dance
on your wedding night.

18:06.640 --> 18:07.598
I don't know how.

18:07.728 --> 18:08.991
So you must learn.

18:09.120 --> 18:10.339
"The French view the Italians

18:10.469 --> 18:11.731
with suspicion..."

18:11.861 --> 18:13.341
[person]
Foot goes out. Wrists go up.

18:13.470 --> 18:14.907
Foot goes around.

18:15.038 --> 18:16.474
"...as known poisoners..."

18:16.605 --> 18:18.085
[person]
We step out with the right.

18:18.215 --> 18:19.826
- Mm-hmm.
- Bring our left to our right.

18:19.955 --> 18:21.609
And a little rise up and down.

18:21.739 --> 18:23.089
"...who are overly emotional

18:23.216 --> 18:25.479
and more interested in art
than conquest."

18:25.566 --> 18:29.440
The French are unfamiliar
with the fork.

18:29.570 --> 18:30.571
How do they eat?

18:30.703 --> 18:32.052
[chuckles] No idea.

18:32.180 --> 18:33.398
With their hands, presumably.

18:33.531 --> 18:35.228
Right and left.

18:35.357 --> 18:37.185
And right, together. Rise.

18:37.315 --> 18:40.797
You will demonstrate, like so.

18:40.970 --> 18:43.364
♪ ♪

18:50.369 --> 18:52.240
Do you really think
this is going to work?

18:52.369 --> 18:53.761
What choice do we have?

18:56.461 --> 18:57.854
It's not enough.

19:00.766 --> 19:01.855
Did you say something?

19:03.813 --> 19:04.814
Yes.

19:06.467 --> 19:08.295
I said it is not enough.

19:08.425 --> 19:10.384
As if you have
ever worn anything finer.

19:10.512 --> 19:13.515
No, I have not. [Sighs]

19:13.647 --> 19:16.128
The marriage is not
a foregone conclusion,

19:16.258 --> 19:17.477
despite what the king thinks.

19:17.604 --> 19:20.172
The French don't like Italians.

19:20.302 --> 19:22.260
The common opinion
is that we are backward,

19:22.392 --> 19:24.960
impractical,
and overly emotional.

19:25.088 --> 19:26.481
They especially won't like one
without royal blood.

19:29.177 --> 19:30.004
I'm not beautiful.

19:31.876 --> 19:32.877
I'm not refined.

19:34.878 --> 19:37.184
If the people of France
are to accept

19:37.273 --> 19:40.450
the orphan child of a most
despised family in Europe,

19:40.578 --> 19:43.102
we must distract them
with finery.

19:46.845 --> 19:48.760
Unless, of course, this is
the best that you can do.

19:50.976 --> 19:53.892
With the budget I was allowed,
no one could have done better.

19:53.979 --> 19:56.459
Well, then the budget
must be raised...

19:58.287 --> 19:59.941
...because it is not enough.

20:01.637 --> 20:03.204
Unless, of course,
you want to end up

20:03.334 --> 20:05.336
hanging by our feet
in the Campo de' Fiori.

20:05.422 --> 20:06.902
- Right, Uncle?
- [Clement] Mm.

20:08.815 --> 20:10.730
We'll get him what he needs.

20:15.170 --> 20:16.606
[cardinal] But, Your Grace,
with the retinue,

20:16.734 --> 20:17.953
the dowry, the trousseau,

20:18.086 --> 20:19.217
we simply don't have the budget.

20:19.347 --> 20:21.001
[Clement]
Well, then peddle indulgences

20:21.129 --> 20:22.348
to some of your wealthy friends

20:22.478 --> 20:25.177
who like fiddling
with little boys.

20:25.307 --> 20:27.222
I don't care what you do,
but raise it,

20:27.309 --> 20:29.050
because the girl
may not know her place,

20:29.136 --> 20:31.051
but she happens to be right.

20:33.010 --> 20:35.142
[Catherine]
Once I asserted my will,

20:35.272 --> 20:37.274
the preparations proceeded
more smoothly.

20:37.402 --> 20:40.318
[exciting music plays]

20:40.406 --> 20:43.148
[indistinct chatter]

20:43.321 --> 20:46.063
♪ ♪

21:04.249 --> 21:05.729
Then came the task

21:05.858 --> 21:07.425
of selecting
the rest of my retinue

21:07.556 --> 21:08.818
to accompany me to France.

21:11.599 --> 21:14.951
I was hoping to introduce you
to Silvestro Niccolini,

21:15.039 --> 21:17.476
the top perfumer in Florence,
but he has taken ill...

21:17.604 --> 21:19.128
quite suddenly, I understand...

21:19.260 --> 21:21.219
so in his stead, his daughter...

21:21.347 --> 21:22.696
Angelica.

21:22.826 --> 21:24.306
I'm sorry my father
couldn't be here.

21:24.436 --> 21:26.351
Stomach ailment.

21:26.482 --> 21:28.701
Potentially fatal, tragically.

21:28.786 --> 21:29.962
What happened to your eye?

21:30.094 --> 21:31.966
Walked into a door.

21:32.052 --> 21:33.749
Clumsy of me.

21:33.878 --> 21:36.446
My father is so patient.

21:36.532 --> 21:39.448
I have made a blend especially
for the duchessina's wedding.

21:39.579 --> 21:40.623
- What's in it?
- [Angelica] Lavender,

21:40.755 --> 21:41.974
benzyl alcohol,

21:42.104 --> 21:43.366
camphor,

21:43.494 --> 21:45.365
ethanol.

21:45.453 --> 21:47.064
Could any of those
cause stomach ailments?

21:47.195 --> 21:48.718
Potentially.

21:48.845 --> 21:50.760
Perhaps I could use
someone like you.

21:50.890 --> 21:51.935
I'm at your service.

21:55.808 --> 21:57.071
If you're a friend
to the oppressed,

21:57.158 --> 21:59.551
you can expect loyalty
in return.

21:59.636 --> 22:00.594
[person clears throat]

22:02.203 --> 22:03.726
Ah, heathen.

22:03.858 --> 22:05.773
[chuckles]

22:05.902 --> 22:07.687
I did her conversion myself.

22:10.079 --> 22:14.170
[gentle music playing]

22:14.299 --> 22:15.431
[Catherine]
I thought I could use someone

22:15.562 --> 22:17.129
who knew
how to charm powerful men.

22:19.824 --> 22:21.522
She'll be a testament to you.

22:24.350 --> 22:25.786
[clears throat]

22:25.916 --> 22:28.745
You should know
that France is a shithole.

22:28.874 --> 22:31.137
But if you
play your cards right,

22:31.269 --> 22:34.185
you could be a princess
in that shithole,

22:34.313 --> 22:38.622
which on balance beats
being a commoner here any day.

22:38.751 --> 22:41.189
[Catherine] Then I encountered
some familiar faces.

22:41.322 --> 22:42.193
[Clement] What do you do?

22:44.802 --> 22:46.021
[laughs]

22:46.150 --> 22:47.586
I love a juggling dwarf.

22:50.372 --> 22:51.547
You don't know how to juggle?

22:51.676 --> 22:53.200
What difference does it make?

22:53.329 --> 22:55.244
Whatever I do,
people find it amusing.

22:55.330 --> 22:57.332
I could pass gas,
and people'd find it funny.

22:57.416 --> 22:59.723
It's true.
It is really most amusing.

22:59.854 --> 23:01.465
People are idiots.

23:01.595 --> 23:03.815
Now... no.

23:03.945 --> 23:04.990
She will be my fool.

23:05.119 --> 23:06.424
Ah, as you wish.

23:06.513 --> 23:07.949
[sighs]

23:08.077 --> 23:09.600
Unless you'd rather stay here.

23:15.955 --> 23:17.348
I know you.

23:17.476 --> 23:18.346
[person clears throat]

23:19.826 --> 23:22.176
Ah, Duchessina Caterina,
of course.

23:22.305 --> 23:25.569
I needed your help,
and you left me to die.

23:25.700 --> 23:27.746
Well, I didn't die.
Too bad for you.

23:27.831 --> 23:30.616
On the contrary,
I made a prediction.

23:30.702 --> 23:33.357
And evidently,
that prediction came true.

23:33.488 --> 23:35.098
You didn't need my help.

23:36.403 --> 23:38.318
Tell me my fortune now.

23:42.972 --> 23:44.365
I think you see as well as I do.

23:46.194 --> 23:47.587
If you learn to use your powers,

23:47.717 --> 23:49.241
you will achieve greatness.

23:49.370 --> 23:52.069
[dramatic music plays]

23:52.241 --> 23:55.418
♪ ♪

23:55.549 --> 23:58.509
I am to travel to France
to marry the king's son.

23:58.636 --> 24:02.118
I want you to join me
as my personal magician.

24:02.204 --> 24:03.640
There are magicians in France.

24:03.773 --> 24:04.513
I want him.

24:07.948 --> 24:09.123
[sighs]

24:09.252 --> 24:11.167
You are a willful girl.

24:11.297 --> 24:14.170
But in my limited experience,

24:14.300 --> 24:16.911
marriage requires the bride

24:16.997 --> 24:19.087
to be a blank canvas.

24:19.172 --> 24:20.651
From here on, everything depends

24:20.784 --> 24:22.829
on your total submission.

24:22.958 --> 24:24.873
And if your new husband
wishes you

24:25.002 --> 24:27.396
to read the scriptures
with him every night,

24:27.485 --> 24:29.487
you will be
his pious little mouse.

24:31.269 --> 24:33.009
And if he wishes you
to sodomize him

24:33.098 --> 24:34.447
with his mother's hairbrush,

24:34.533 --> 24:35.838
you will do that.

24:37.056 --> 24:39.841
It is your sacred duty.

24:39.971 --> 24:41.364
But remember that you serve

24:41.451 --> 24:43.061
a higher authority in heaven...

24:44.585 --> 24:47.240
...represented on Earth by me.

24:49.370 --> 24:51.459
May I inquire,
is the dowry complete?

24:52.761 --> 24:54.589
How dare you?

24:54.720 --> 24:56.200
Of course it's complete.

24:56.329 --> 24:57.852
[chuckles]

24:58.463 --> 24:59.768
Then we shouldn't
have a problem.

25:06.163 --> 25:09.035
[Rahima] So you never
saw your home again?

25:09.167 --> 25:09.994
[Catherine] No.

25:11.688 --> 25:12.907
Come to think of it, I didn't.

25:14.474 --> 25:16.258
[Rahima]
I'm sorry to hear that.

25:16.389 --> 25:18.739
Oh, don't be.

25:18.870 --> 25:22.135
Nostalgia is no friend
to people like us.

25:22.306 --> 25:24.917
♪ ♪

25:25.047 --> 25:27.963
Truth is, I never
really liked it that much.

25:30.747 --> 25:33.532
♪ ♪

26:45.758 --> 26:48.457
[breathing heavily]

26:50.544 --> 26:51.806
It's like a giant goose egg.

26:51.937 --> 26:54.679
- Typical Italian gaudiness.
- Mm.

26:54.811 --> 26:56.769
[clears throat]

26:56.895 --> 26:57.765
[Eleanor] Oh, here we are.

26:59.116 --> 27:01.118
Buongiorno!

27:01.248 --> 27:04.033
- Welcome, uh, Italy.
- [laughter]

27:04.164 --> 27:06.297
Your Majesty.

27:15.085 --> 27:18.349
[laughter]

27:24.353 --> 27:26.573
[Clement]
May I present my niece,

27:26.704 --> 27:29.490
the duchessina
Caterina de' Medici,

27:29.619 --> 27:32.231
as a prospective bride
for your son,

27:32.359 --> 27:34.013
the duke of Orléans?

27:34.142 --> 27:35.753
What is it?

27:35.883 --> 27:37.972
Some sort of aquatic slug?

27:38.102 --> 27:40.278
[laughter]

27:40.365 --> 27:43.760
Not the one I have to marry,
thank God.

27:43.845 --> 27:45.673
What's she got stuck
to her feet?

27:49.546 --> 27:51.548
There is the question
of the dowry.

27:53.895 --> 27:56.724
[horse whinnies]

28:01.728 --> 28:04.862
You are short
the amount we agreed upon.

28:05.992 --> 28:07.167
He lied to me.

28:07.297 --> 28:08.559
[Clement]
That is an installment

28:08.690 --> 28:10.692
with more to follow.

28:10.823 --> 28:14.262
It's dangerous to travel with
huge sums on the high seas.

28:14.390 --> 28:16.174
The remaining balance
will be dispatched

28:16.305 --> 28:18.046
as soon as I return to Florence.

28:18.176 --> 28:19.743
Pay no attention.

28:19.873 --> 28:23.268
The duke of Guise,
like the rest of his family,

28:23.398 --> 28:25.052
thinks only of money.

28:25.137 --> 28:26.486
[Charles] As a... [clears throat]

28:26.616 --> 28:28.705
As a convert
to the Protestant faith,

28:28.834 --> 28:30.619
I, of course,
place no value whatsoever

28:30.748 --> 28:32.402
on worldly possessions.

28:32.534 --> 28:35.928
However, we would not
want your subjects

28:36.056 --> 28:37.623
thinking the Valois court
was in the business

28:37.753 --> 28:40.278
of bargain hunting, would we?

28:40.407 --> 28:41.800
[laughter]

28:41.929 --> 28:43.714
[Francis] Um, Francois,

28:43.845 --> 28:47.675
this is a teachable moment,
I think, hmm?

28:48.849 --> 28:52.505
Do we trust the pope
to pay the rest of the dowry

28:52.591 --> 28:55.072
and proceed as planned,

28:55.158 --> 28:57.639
or do we
call the whole thing off

28:57.768 --> 28:59.814
to save our reputation, hmm?

28:59.944 --> 29:01.511
What would you do

29:01.641 --> 29:05.819
if I were dead and gone
and you were already king?

29:07.209 --> 29:09.647
If it were a thing of beauty,
we could overlook such things,

29:09.777 --> 29:12.650
but it most certainly is not.

29:12.780 --> 29:14.695
[Francis] No need
to make it personal, son.

29:22.004 --> 29:24.702
My uncle, His Grace the pope,
is too modest.

29:24.832 --> 29:27.965
He is also offering
the Duchy of Urbino

29:28.094 --> 29:29.922
with its wealth of farmland...

29:30.052 --> 29:31.532
[softly] What are you saying?

29:31.664 --> 29:34.841
and a cardinalship
to the Guises' second son,

29:34.970 --> 29:37.103
a sign
of the Vatican's appreciation

29:37.232 --> 29:39.322
of the family's
staunch Catholicism

29:39.450 --> 29:42.148
and forgiveness

29:42.280 --> 29:44.369
of the Bourbon family's
abandonment of the church.

29:44.498 --> 29:45.890
God forgives you.

29:46.022 --> 29:47.023
- [chuckles]
- Hmm.

29:47.150 --> 29:51.154
But only if this union be
the will of God,

29:51.286 --> 29:53.070
Your Grace.

29:53.200 --> 29:54.593
Bit over the top,
don't you think?

29:54.723 --> 29:56.508
His opinion didn't matter.

29:56.637 --> 29:58.639
This was strictly
for the Catholics of the house.

29:58.771 --> 30:02.644
A good Catholic girl is exactly
what this court needs, hmm?

30:02.729 --> 30:04.078
[Charles]
If you say so, Your Majesty.

30:06.777 --> 30:08.082
[Francis sighs]

30:11.390 --> 30:14.480
We happily accept
your increase in the dowry.

30:18.960 --> 30:23.660
France accepts the duchessina
Catherine de Medici

30:23.744 --> 30:26.573
in marriage with their son,

30:26.705 --> 30:29.185
Henri, duke of Orléans.

30:29.314 --> 30:31.142
- [Eleanor] Lovely.
- [Clement] Congratulations.

30:31.271 --> 30:32.447
You've made Urbino French

30:32.534 --> 30:34.144
and the match has been accepted.

30:34.274 --> 30:35.885
But don't think
we're in the clear.

30:36.013 --> 30:38.102
You have to stay in favor
long enough to get pregnant.

30:38.233 --> 30:41.192
Do you think
you can manage that, hmm?

30:41.322 --> 30:43.629
- Hmm.
- [Catherine chuckles dryly]

30:43.760 --> 30:46.676
Well, shall we go
and meet the groom?

30:46.807 --> 30:48.069
[horse whinnying]

30:48.153 --> 30:50.851
[indistinct chatter]

30:57.944 --> 31:01.252
There he is, my second son.

31:01.382 --> 31:02.992
[Montmorency] His athletic
skills have developed nicely.

31:03.122 --> 31:04.950
Really?

31:05.036 --> 31:05.994
[Montmorency]
Henri is dedicating his win

31:06.082 --> 31:07.649
to Diane de Poitiers.

31:07.776 --> 31:09.430
A relation of yours, I believe?

31:09.564 --> 31:11.609
A cousin,
though we've never met.

31:11.739 --> 31:14.263
Diane has been like a mother
to my boy

31:14.394 --> 31:16.439
ever since
his own mother passed on.

31:18.308 --> 31:19.745
Then something terrible
happened...

31:22.266 --> 31:23.963
the worst thing that could
happen to someone like us.

31:26.010 --> 31:27.925
I fell in love.

31:28.053 --> 31:30.926
[Francis] My second son,
Henri, duke of Orléans.

31:34.581 --> 31:35.582
You're much nicer to look at
in real life

31:35.667 --> 31:37.146
than your portrait.

31:37.279 --> 31:38.541
[Catherine chuckles politely]

31:38.670 --> 31:40.019
[Henri] Duchessina.

31:40.150 --> 31:41.282
Your Majesty.

31:41.410 --> 31:42.411
[Montmorency] Impressive.

31:42.498 --> 31:43.890
You rode well.

31:43.979 --> 31:46.155
[Henri] As you taught me.

31:46.285 --> 31:47.460
Did you watch the joust, Father?

31:48.633 --> 31:50.156
I did not.

31:50.242 --> 31:52.331
One joust is the same
as the next to me.

31:52.464 --> 31:54.379
[chuckles]

31:54.509 --> 31:58.730
My son is always practicing war.

31:58.859 --> 32:00.991
When I was his age,
I was leading armies.

32:01.123 --> 32:02.559
[chuckles]

32:02.689 --> 32:05.213
Um...

32:05.342 --> 32:07.693
you kids go and have fun, hmm?

32:07.821 --> 32:10.128
Uh, get to know each other.

32:10.256 --> 32:12.171
After all,
you will be married, hmm?

32:17.829 --> 32:19.222
[laughter]

32:19.350 --> 32:20.439
- I'm so sorry.
- [Catherine] It's okay.

32:20.570 --> 32:21.876
[yawns] Right.

32:22.005 --> 32:25.835
Um, yes, I'm gonna get this off.

32:26.879 --> 32:28.228
Come with me.
I-I'm gonna show you the pond,

32:28.358 --> 32:28.968
- if you don't mind.
- [Catherine] Mm-hmm.

32:29.096 --> 32:30.010
[Henri] It's, um...

32:30.098 --> 32:32.187
[tender music plays]

32:32.318 --> 32:33.667
[sighs]

32:33.841 --> 32:36.496
♪ ♪

32:44.543 --> 32:45.631
[Catherine]
Are they really necessary?

32:45.719 --> 32:47.155
My father insists.

32:48.590 --> 32:49.983
I see.

32:50.070 --> 32:52.464
I can look after myself,
mind you,

32:52.592 --> 32:54.159
um, not that I can imagine
one of my subjects

32:54.290 --> 32:55.378
meaning me any harm.

32:55.508 --> 32:56.640
[Catherine] Certainly not.

32:56.728 --> 32:57.642
[Henri]
Or you, for that matter,

32:57.771 --> 32:59.556
now that, um...

32:59.643 --> 33:00.774
that this, um...

33:03.212 --> 33:05.040
- I'm sorry.
- [Catherine] It's all right.

33:05.170 --> 33:06.824
[Henri] ...n-now that this
treaty between our two nations

33:06.951 --> 33:08.213
has been forged.

33:09.478 --> 33:10.870
Bring Charles V to heel.

33:12.087 --> 33:12.957
[Catherine chuckles]

33:14.697 --> 33:16.394
"Treaty."

33:16.524 --> 33:18.134
He was too shy
to say the word "marriage."

33:19.440 --> 33:21.355
Sweet, no?

33:22.747 --> 33:24.966
It was a cunning move on behalf
of your father and my uncle.

33:25.096 --> 33:26.967
I thought so as well.

33:27.879 --> 33:29.228
You seem very close
to Madame de Poitiers.

33:29.360 --> 33:31.493
Mm-hmm, she's...

33:31.624 --> 33:33.017
yeah, she's a wonderful woman.

33:33.144 --> 33:35.582
She's, um...
she's taught me so much.

33:36.537 --> 33:38.713
She's my cousin.

33:38.846 --> 33:40.021
- Really?
- [Catherine] Yeah.

33:40.151 --> 33:40.891
Really? She's your cousin?

33:41.021 --> 33:42.326
Mm-hmm.

33:44.458 --> 33:45.851
Oh, well, no wonder
we get along so well, then.

33:45.981 --> 33:47.243
[chuckles]

33:48.982 --> 33:50.854
- Oh, sugar.
- [Catherine gasps] Oh!

33:52.595 --> 33:53.813
- Oh.
- [Henri] No, no, no, no.

33:56.335 --> 33:57.467
- [Catherine] No, no.
- [Henri] It's a big one.

33:57.598 --> 33:59.164
- Hey, come on. Pick him up.
- Oh, go on.

33:59.295 --> 34:00.818
[Henri]
He's tiny and he's sweet.

34:00.948 --> 34:03.254
And he wants to say hello.
Hey, come on.

34:03.385 --> 34:04.995
Uh, you got him?

34:05.124 --> 34:06.081
[Catherine] Yeah.

34:06.213 --> 34:08.170
Uh, sing to it.

34:08.300 --> 34:09.475
- [Catherine] What?
- Sing to it.

34:09.605 --> 34:11.389
I have a terrible voice.

34:11.521 --> 34:13.000
I doubt that very much.

34:13.085 --> 34:13.826
[chuckles]

34:16.437 --> 34:19.179
[vocalizing softly]

34:19.351 --> 34:22.181
♪ ♪

34:28.185 --> 34:30.143
- [Henry] Go on.
- Wow. Mm.

34:30.271 --> 34:31.664
A-a trick I learned as a boy.

34:33.799 --> 34:34.974
All animals are musical.

34:35.103 --> 34:35.975
It's, um...

34:38.190 --> 34:39.802
...it's the uh, last thing
my-my mother taught me

34:39.933 --> 34:41.065
before she died.

34:42.762 --> 34:44.197
I never knew my mother.

34:44.371 --> 34:47.158
♪ ♪

34:50.637 --> 34:52.856
I will always believe,

34:52.943 --> 34:55.032
for that one day at least,
that my love was requited.

34:58.556 --> 35:00.122
Nobody can tell me it wasn't.

35:02.122 --> 35:03.254
[chuckles]

35:06.603 --> 35:09.214
[Catherine] And like that,
we were married.

35:09.348 --> 35:12.090
[bells tolling]

35:12.263 --> 35:15.048
♪ ♪

35:19.658 --> 35:22.443
[bright music playing]

35:22.617 --> 35:24.184
♪ ♪

35:24.312 --> 35:26.271
You look very beautiful
this evening.

35:26.403 --> 35:28.231
- Thanks. Thank you.
- Mm-hmm.

35:31.319 --> 35:32.233
[sighs]

35:36.496 --> 35:38.629
Oh, hello, cousin.

35:38.758 --> 35:39.802
Madame de Poitiers.

35:39.935 --> 35:41.719
[chuckles] Call me Diane.

35:41.848 --> 35:43.023
We're family, after all.

35:43.109 --> 35:44.980
Yeah, of course.

35:45.111 --> 35:47.722
Um, I'm so pleased
to have a relative at court.

35:47.853 --> 35:50.551
Mm, your mother
would be very happy

35:50.680 --> 35:52.420
if she could see you now.

35:52.550 --> 35:54.421
You remember my mother?

35:54.554 --> 35:55.903
But of course.

35:56.032 --> 35:57.642
On her wedding night.

35:57.730 --> 36:01.081
Such a beauty, just like you.

36:01.210 --> 36:02.167
[Catherine chuckles]

36:02.296 --> 36:04.167
I feel very lucky.

36:04.299 --> 36:06.083
Henri seems
such a fine young man.

36:06.215 --> 36:08.870
He's the best man I know.

36:12.434 --> 36:13.784
I love your dress.

36:13.914 --> 36:15.394
[Diane]
I always wear black and white

36:15.523 --> 36:18.048
since my husband died.

36:18.176 --> 36:20.614
Mixed feelings,
I suppose you could say.

36:20.747 --> 36:23.620
- I'm sorry.
- Well, don't be.

36:23.746 --> 36:28.098
A widow is the best thing
a woman can hope to be.

36:28.230 --> 36:30.798
You get to keep the money.

36:30.926 --> 36:32.885
And if you are
sufficiently devout,

36:32.971 --> 36:36.235
no one expects you
to take another husband.

36:36.322 --> 36:39.281
It is the closest thing
we have to freedom.

36:42.108 --> 36:44.589
If I weren't so fond of Henri,

36:44.720 --> 36:46.112
I'd wish you the same.

36:46.242 --> 36:49.332
[both chuckle]

36:49.461 --> 36:52.856
Perhaps you'd like a guide
of the local flora and fauna.

36:52.985 --> 36:54.421
- Oh, yes, please.
- Mm.

36:54.552 --> 36:56.903
Queen Eleanor,

36:57.035 --> 36:58.994
sister of France's mortal enemy,

36:59.121 --> 37:00.993
the Holy Roman Emperor.

37:01.123 --> 37:03.778
She'd rather go to bed
with a dog than a king.

37:03.909 --> 37:05.824
[gasps] Oh.

37:05.911 --> 37:07.869
Not that it matters.

37:07.955 --> 37:10.392
Francis.

37:10.521 --> 37:13.002
Lately, he's been very busy
with his latest conquest,

37:13.132 --> 37:14.656
Anne D'Etampes,

37:14.785 --> 37:17.005
said to be capable
of unspeakable things

37:17.135 --> 37:17.832
in the bedroom.

37:20.096 --> 37:22.576
Charles of Bourbon.

37:22.705 --> 37:26.666
Like most true aristocrats,
he's not very bright.

37:26.795 --> 37:29.058
What in God's name
is this contraption?

37:29.190 --> 37:31.540
Converted to Protestantism

37:31.670 --> 37:33.759
purely for political gain.

37:33.888 --> 37:35.890
Must be Italian.

37:36.019 --> 37:38.717
Then you have the duke
of Guise with his sons.

37:38.847 --> 37:41.153
His title is bought
and paid for.

37:41.284 --> 37:42.589
Merchant's daughter.

37:42.720 --> 37:44.200
I'd rather have my knees broken

37:44.328 --> 37:46.330
than to bend it to the Medici.

37:46.460 --> 37:49.681
Mm, well, I'm sure
that can be arranged.

37:49.811 --> 37:52.466
You've met Montmorency,
the king's loyal dog.

37:52.596 --> 37:54.598
Clever to Francis
to invite the sultan.

37:54.729 --> 37:57.427
Everyone knows
it was your idea, Montmorency.

37:57.557 --> 37:59.820
The rest of Europe is actually
fucking terrified of him.

37:59.951 --> 38:01.866
- Useful ally, wouldn't you say?
- Mm.

38:01.995 --> 38:04.041
[Diane] Together,
they form the Privy Council,

38:04.170 --> 38:06.216
and they despise each other.

38:06.344 --> 38:08.346
The only thing
they have in common

38:08.477 --> 38:11.219
is, they'd put a knife in
the king's back for the crown.

38:11.348 --> 38:13.350
[applause]

38:13.481 --> 38:15.439
[Clement] How much longer
can this possibly go on?

38:16.964 --> 38:18.487
[clears throat]

38:18.614 --> 38:20.399
I would like
to offer a benediction.

38:21.965 --> 38:24.489
To the couple's
eternal happiness,

38:24.575 --> 38:27.404
as God in heaven intended it.

38:27.534 --> 38:30.059
And I would like
to propose a toast.

38:30.188 --> 38:33.931
To the unity
of France and Italy.

38:34.061 --> 38:37.368
A new era of peace
and prosperity.

38:38.586 --> 38:39.630
[Clement] God willing.

38:39.719 --> 38:42.547
[gentle music playing]

38:42.633 --> 38:45.419
♪ ♪

39:09.260 --> 39:10.522
Hey, go dance with your cousin.

39:24.186 --> 39:25.535
[Diane] Tonight's
your wedding night, cousin.

39:27.055 --> 39:28.796
You know
what is expected of you.

39:28.929 --> 39:30.017
[Catherine] Mm.

39:31.929 --> 39:33.278
Let me give you
a piece of advice.

39:34.845 --> 39:37.369
Do not let your husband fail.

39:39.937 --> 39:40.633
[Catherine chuckles]

39:43.158 --> 39:44.507
I know him well.

39:46.941 --> 39:47.942
Be yourself.

39:49.552 --> 39:51.162
Be bold.

39:51.249 --> 39:52.773
That's what Henri wants.

39:54.296 --> 39:55.514
[Catherine] Yeah.

39:55.642 --> 39:57.122
Yes, I will.

39:59.343 --> 40:01.955
We are all depending on you.

40:02.127 --> 40:04.869
♪ ♪

40:09.130 --> 40:10.044
- [fireworks popping]
- [person] Did you see that?

40:10.175 --> 40:11.742
[Diane] Oh!

40:11.872 --> 40:12.742
- [laughs]
- [Henri] Let's see.

40:12.873 --> 40:15.658
[excited chatter]

40:32.236 --> 40:32.889
[Catherine] Oh.

40:46.159 --> 40:48.857
[people murmuring]

40:57.122 --> 40:58.776
Bold, hmm?

40:58.907 --> 41:00.517
[Catherine] Hmm.

41:00.604 --> 41:02.954
[yawns]

41:03.085 --> 41:06.305
[person] Oh, pretty.

41:06.434 --> 41:07.304
[person] Very pretty.

41:14.308 --> 41:16.267
- [Francis] Let the joust begin!
- [Clement] Mm.

41:18.483 --> 41:19.223
[Clement clears throat]

41:23.139 --> 41:24.532
[person] Rather him than me.

41:24.620 --> 41:27.318
[indistinct chatter]

41:31.667 --> 41:33.234
[Clement clears throat]

41:51.381 --> 41:53.644
Someone will have
to take initiative, I think.

41:53.773 --> 41:54.513
[Eleanor] Mm.

42:08.435 --> 42:09.828
[person] Wow, adventurous.

42:12.394 --> 42:13.961
[Charles] Germanic position.

42:14.092 --> 42:15.224
It's a safe bet.

42:16.311 --> 42:17.878
[softly] Hey, look at me.

42:18.008 --> 42:19.009
Pretend we're alone.

42:23.010 --> 42:25.795
[grunting softly]

42:27.276 --> 42:28.103
Ow.

42:33.848 --> 42:34.762
[Clement] Well, they're...

42:36.718 --> 42:37.676
- Now...
- [Francis] Here we go.

42:44.810 --> 42:46.900
[Henri moans]

42:47.029 --> 42:48.901
[Catherine whimpers]

43:04.477 --> 43:05.565
[Clement] There you go.

43:09.391 --> 43:10.915
[Charles] Well done.

43:11.046 --> 43:13.614
- [applause]
- [person] Bravo!

43:13.742 --> 43:15.092
[person] It's no conquest.

43:15.178 --> 43:17.702
- [Francis] A good joust.
- [Clement] Mm.

43:17.834 --> 43:20.925
[Francis] But, uh, in bed,

43:21.052 --> 43:22.749
you are not the winner,
mon fils.

43:22.838 --> 43:24.666
[laughter]

43:24.796 --> 43:25.579
Well done.

43:36.066 --> 43:37.024
Henri.

43:37.936 --> 43:38.806
[softly] Get out.

43:40.894 --> 43:42.113
What?

43:42.244 --> 43:42.984
[Henri] Did you not hear me?

43:43.069 --> 43:44.157
I said get out!

43:45.071 --> 43:45.854
[Catherine] Okay.

43:52.729 --> 43:55.427
[unsettling music plays]

43:55.600 --> 43:58.386
♪ ♪

44:13.050 --> 44:15.443
[wine pouring]

44:17.356 --> 44:18.357
Drink this.

44:21.753 --> 44:22.972
Principessa.

44:23.144 --> 44:25.929
♪ ♪

44:33.849 --> 44:34.676
Henri.

44:39.244 --> 44:42.029
[sinister music plays]

44:42.202 --> 44:44.988
♪ ♪

45:00.648 --> 45:02.737
They were lovers?

45:02.867 --> 45:03.868
Yes.

45:06.957 --> 45:08.567
And you know
what I learned that day?

45:09.742 --> 45:12.093
That you could overcome

45:12.222 --> 45:15.486
every obstacle
put in front of you

45:15.618 --> 45:19.317
but you couldn't win the heart
of the one you loved?

45:20.534 --> 45:21.883
No.

45:25.754 --> 45:29.671
I learned
never to trust a single soul.

45:31.804 --> 45:35.286
[tense music plays]

45:35.413 --> 45:37.633
Take this clumsy girl away.

45:37.720 --> 45:39.548
[Rahima] No, it wasn't me!

45:39.679 --> 45:40.593
It wasn't...

45:40.722 --> 45:41.940
This is a mistake.

45:43.506 --> 45:45.769
Where are you taking me?

45:45.900 --> 45:47.423
Where are you taking me?
Please!

45:47.553 --> 45:48.945
Let go of me! It wasn't me!

45:49.076 --> 45:51.557
I'm sorry! I'm... I'm sorry! No!

45:51.642 --> 45:52.686
[grunts]

45:52.861 --> 45:55.603
♪ ♪

45:56.950 --> 45:59.388
I didn't do anything.

45:59.519 --> 46:00.781
Come on. I didn't do anything.

